{"title":"Wolf Tooth Introduces New eBike Chainrings for Shimano & Trek TQ Motors","link":"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-ebike-chainrings-shimano-trek/","date":1685137323000,"content":"<p>To all eBiking Wolf Toothers: Your moment has come.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Wolf Tooth direct mount chainrings for Shimano eBike motors have a 55mm chainline and are compatible with all Boost and Super Boost bikes that use the Shimano EP8, E8000, and E7000 e-bike motor splines.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That gives Shimano pedal-assisters a <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/?s=wolf+tooth\" target=\"_blank\">Wolf Tooth option</a>, which comes in 32 and 34t sizes and, of course, with Drop-Stop teeth.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/WT_ST_SH-E-32T_01_1200x.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/WT_ST_SH-E-32T_01_1200x-800x800.webp\" alt=\"wolf tooth chainring for shimano ebike motors\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/WT_ST_SH-E-32T_01_1200x-800x800.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/WT_ST_SH-E-32T_01_1200x-297x297.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/WT_ST_SH-E-32T_01_1200x-120x120.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/WT_ST_SH-E-32T_01_1200x-768x768.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/WT_ST_SH-E-32T_01_1200x.webp 1200w\" /></a><figcaption>Compatible with Shimano mid-drive motors</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Use Drop-Stop ST for use with Shimano 12-speed Hyperglide+ and 12-speed KMC chains. Use Drop-Stop B for all 9, 10, and 11-speed chains or 12-speed SRAM Eagle, SRAM Flattop Road or Transmission (T-Type), KMC, Connex, or Wippermann chains.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/DROPSTOP_A_B_ST_v3-1-scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"461\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/DROPSTOP_A_B_ST_v3-1-800x461.webp\" alt=\"wolf tooth drop stop compatibility chart\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/DROPSTOP_A_B_ST_v3-1-800x461.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/DROPSTOP_A_B_ST_v3-1-297x171.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/DROPSTOP_A_B_ST_v3-1-120x69.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/DROPSTOP_A_B_ST_v3-1-768x443.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/DROPSTOP_A_B_ST_v3-1-1536x886.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/DROPSTOP_A_B_ST_v3-1-2048x1181.webp 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>Tooth layout compatibility</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But what about riders cranking other mid-drive rigs?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Wolf Tooth doesn’t stop at Shimano — it also dropped direct mount rings compatible with TQ motors found on Trek ebikes like the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/trek-fuel-exe-emtb/\" target=\"_blank\">new Fuel EXe</a>. These come in 30 or 32t.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/WT_TQ32-ST_02_1200x.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/WT_TQ32-ST_02_1200x-800x800.webp\" alt=\"wolf tooth trek ebike chainring\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/WT_TQ32-ST_02_1200x-800x800.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/WT_TQ32-ST_02_1200x-297x297.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/WT_TQ32-ST_02_1200x-120x120.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/WT_TQ32-ST_02_1200x-768x768.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/WT_TQ32-ST_02_1200x.webp 1200w\" /></a><figcaption>Trek motor compatibility</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Prices for the eBike rings are on the upper end of Wolf Tooth average. You’ll pay $85 MSRP for each unit. Like all of their chainrings, Wolf Tooth manufactures these in the United States.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.wolftoothcomponents.com/collections/chainrings?gclid=CjwKCAjwscGjBhAXEiwAswQqNJ6ODT5w4sEhyXb-OIlr3T43pVfYhyoV-WMedGFk4o4DCH4NTEp47BoCh7kQAvD_BwE\" target=\"_blank\">woolftoothcomponenets.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wolf-tooth-ebike-chainrings-shimano-trek/\">Wolf Tooth Introduces New eBike Chainrings for Shimano &amp; Trek TQ Motors</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Sam Anderson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"9f2bb1356f9b52c396d52a9b392b57a35abdbfc3c96fcdbdd6d8fbeca0195c3f","category":"Cycling"}